The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, gave a speech at the White House in honor of the March for Life event. He praised the pro-life movement and thanked those in attendance for their dedication and efforts. Pence highlighted the actions taken by the Trump administration in support of the pro-life cause, such as reinstating the Mexico City policy and defunding Planned Parenthood. He also mentioned that President Trump would be the first president in history to address the March for Life. Pence expressed his belief that the pro-life movement is making progress and that America will restore the sanctity of life in its laws. He ended his speech by thanking everyone for their commitment and urging them to continue their efforts.